{"data":{"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"12 Feb","startTime":"17h35","speakers":[{"name":"Gonçalo Silva","bio":"Gonçalo is the CTO at Doist, creators of Todoist and Twist. He's been working remotely for over a decade, and managing remote teams for most of that time. He loves long-term ambition, asynchronous communication, and programming.","img":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/f6e95a20b5842e0d2fb971f01fc0a002/6e63d/goncalo_silva.jpg","srcSet":"/static/f6e95a20b5842e0d2fb971f01fc0a002/b315d/goncalo_silva.jpg 100w,\n/static/f6e95a20b5842e0d2fb971f01fc0a002/8295c/goncalo_silva.jpg 200w,\n/static/f6e95a20b5842e0d2fb971f01fc0a002/6e63d/goncalo_silva.jpg 400w,\n/static/f6e95a20b5842e0d2fb971f01fc0a002/7b2a1/goncalo_silva.jpg 600w,\n/static/f6e95a20b5842e0d2fb971f01fc0a002/58c11/goncalo_silva.jpg 750w","sizes":"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"}}}}]}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"13 Feb","startTime":"14h00","speakers":[{"name":"Isabel Costa","bio":"Isabel Costa is a Software Engineer and works at Globality. She is also an admin for AnitaB.org Open Source and GitHub Star. She was a Google Summer of Code (GSoC) student in 2018, and an admin in 2020, as well as a Google Code-in Mentor in 2019. Since participating in GSoC she maintains the project started during the program, helping newcomers make their first contributions or find new ways to contribute to Open Source.","img":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/c4528c2b6084cd08e048016c9accfc02/c74b8/isabel_costa.png","srcSet":"/static/c4528c2b6084cd08e048016c9accfc02/71eb7/isabel_costa.png 100w,\n/static/c4528c2b6084cd08e048016c9accfc02/b3a76/isabel_costa.png 200w,\n/static/c4528c2b6084cd08e048016c9accfc02/c74b8/isabel_costa.png 390w","sizes":"(max-width: 390px) 100vw, 390px"}}}}]}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"12 Feb","startTime":"15h50","speakers":[{"name":"Jean-Baptiste Kempf","bio":"Jean-Baptiste Kempf is the president of the VideoLAN non-profit organization and one of the lead developers of the open source VLC media player. Jean-Baptiste is a 37-year old French engineer and has been part of the VideoLAN community since 2005. Since then, he has worked on or lead most VideoLAN related projects, including VLC for desktop, the relicensing of libVLC, the ports to mobile operating systems, and various multimedia libraries like libdvdcss or libbluray. He also created the legal entity of VideoLAN, a French non-profit organization, in 2008. Jean-Baptiste has also been working in various video-related startups, and founded VideoLabs, a company focusing on open source multimedia technologies.","img":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/2be09cc154842216b3ea1eff4b468362/6e63d/jbkempf.jpg","srcSet":"/static/2be09cc154842216b3ea1eff4b468362/b315d/jbkempf.jpg 100w,\n/static/2be09cc154842216b3ea1eff4b468362/8295c/jbkempf.jpg 200w,\n/static/2be09cc154842216b3ea1eff4b468362/6e63d/jbkempf.jpg 400w,\n/static/2be09cc154842216b3ea1eff4b468362/7b2a1/jbkempf.jpg 600w,\n/static/2be09cc154842216b3ea1eff4b468362/c6eb9/jbkempf.jpg 627w","sizes":"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"}}}}]}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"12 Feb","startTime":"14h15","speakers":[{"name":"Gil Faria","bio":"Gil Faria has a degree in Computer Engineering from the Faculty of Science and Technology, New University of Lisbon. He started programming at age 9, shortly after receiving his first computer, a Commodore 64. Since then, he hasn't been able to stop feeding his interest in Technology and programming. Gil is currently working as an Engineering Manager at Farfetch, focusing on developing high-performance teams, delivering value on time, and guaranteeing quality while promoting a friendly and professional atmosphere.","img":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/bb8f4236aa284e6d3211e002ab1fd068/79531/gil_faria.jpg","srcSet":"/static/bb8f4236aa284e6d3211e002ab1fd068/b315d/gil_faria.jpg 100w,\n/static/bb8f4236aa284e6d3211e002ab1fd068/8295c/gil_faria.jpg 200w,\n/static/bb8f4236aa284e6d3211e002ab1fd068/79531/gil_faria.jpg 220w","sizes":"(max-width: 220px) 100vw, 220px"}}}}]}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"12 Feb","startTime":"16h40","speakers":[{"name":"Fernando Mendes","bio":"Mendes exchanges coffee for code at Subvisual. He has a background in Distributed Systems and Cryptography, having won multiple national awards for academic excellence. Previously at UTrust and thoughtbot, he also does a lot of volunteering, being the founder of \\#include <braga> and a former champion of CoderDojo Braga. '); DROP TABLE speakers; --","img":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/bf471f39e4ebbd64dc94a043f3c92fca/0a8d8/fernando_mendes.png","srcSet":"/static/bf471f39e4ebbd64dc94a043f3c92fca/71eb7/fernando_mendes.png 100w,\n/static/bf471f39e4ebbd64dc94a043f3c92fca/b3a76/fernando_mendes.png 200w,\n/static/bf471f39e4ebbd64dc94a043f3c92fca/0a8d8/fernando_mendes.png 400w,\n/static/bf471f39e4ebbd64dc94a043f3c92fca/b7710/fernando_mendes.png 600w,\n/static/bf471f39e4ebbd64dc94a043f3c92fca/c1282/fernando_mendes.png 800w,\n/static/bf471f39e4ebbd64dc94a043f3c92fca/64ac3/fernando_mendes.png 1638w","sizes":"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"}}}}]}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"date":"12 Feb","startTime":"15h10","speakers":[{"name":"David Sopas","bio":"David Sopas is a security researcher with more than 15 years of experience. Currently David leads a talented team of researchers at Checkmarx and at the same time manages is own security company Char49.  Best known for his published work on finding vulnerabilities for companies like Google, Microsoft, Adobe, eBay, Amazon and many others. Also each year you can find him speaking at local and international security conferences.","img":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/2f85176f0e829cb44ed50cee7da713b1/6e63d/davidsopas.jpg","srcSet":"/static/2f85176f0e829cb44ed50cee7da713b1/b315d/davidsopas.jpg 100w,\n/static/2f85176f0e829cb44ed50cee7da713b1/8295c/davidsopas.jpg 200w,\n/static/2f85176f0e829cb44ed50cee7da713b1/6e63d/davidsopas.jpg 400w,\n/static/2f85176f0e829cb44ed50cee7da713b1/bae4e/davidsopas.jpg 500w","sizes":"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"}}}}]}}}]}}}